1. Run `bosh deployments` to identify the name of your current BOSH deployment:
  <pre class='terminal'>
  $ bosh deployments
  +-------------+--------------+-------------------------------------------------+
  | Name        | Release(s)   | Stemcell(s)                                     |
  +-------------+--------------+-------------------------------------------------+
  | cf-example  | cf-mysql/10  | bosh-vsphere-esxi-ubuntu-trusty-go_agent/2690.3 |
  |             | cf/183.2     |                                                 |
  +-------------+--------------+-------------------------------------------------+
</pre>

1. Run `bosh manifest -d MY-DEPLOYMENT MY-MANIFEST` to download and
save each BOSH deployment manifest. You need this manifest to locate information about your databases.
Repeat these instructions for each manifest.
Replace `MY-DEPLOYMENT` with the name of the current BOSH deployment.
For this procedure, use `cf.yml` as `MY-MANIFEST`.

	<pre class='terminal'>
	$ bosh manifest -d cf-example cf.yml
	Deployment manifest saved to `cf.yml'
	</pre>

1. Place the .yml file in a secure location.
